What you need to know:

Diego Maradona's coffin arrived at the presidential palace in Buenos Aires for a period of lying in state, TV reports showedMourners, many in tears, and many wearing the World Cup winner's number 10 Argentina jersey, gathered at the Casa Rosada presidential palace where the national hero's coffin was draped in the sky blue and white Argentine flagDespite a wave of coronavirus cases in Argentina, fans gathered at landmarks including Buenos Aires' Obelisk monument and Argentinos Juniors' Diego Armando Maradona Stadium, where he started his career